I was reading reviews for places in my neighborhood one weekend a while ago and read that this place was really good. I had always passed it and looking at it from the outside you would never know how cute and clean it is inside. I decided to give it a try and I surely don't regret it one bit. Upon entering it looks like a grocery store, but then as you go further in it's a quaint, little, nicely decorated clean establishment. Their menu consists of authentic Mexican dishes but they also have American and other Latin cuisines. I only ordered a chicken quesadilla and it was really good. The flavor was good. The chicken seasoned very well. They were very nice telling me my food would be coming out shortly every few seconds. I wasn't in a rush because I was admiring the decor of the place. I also noticed the kitchen area and there were pots stacked on shelves that were spotless! The stainless steel was gleaming. I have found a new place that I will get dinner from on those evenings when I don't feel like cooking. I want to try more of the Mexican dishes. I played it safe today. But not next time. I have gone back several times since I first reviewed this place and they made updates to it.  It no longer looks like a grocery store inside. They have a bar note and they updated the seating, ordering area and their menu.  I still enjoy their Mexican dishes.
recently renovated local mexican restaurant. good traditional specialties in a pleasant upscale environment. try the carnitas taco.
